THE Premier Soccer League (PSL) will observe a moment of silence for the people who have lost their lives to the Covid-19 pandemic. This will be followed by applause from the players for the brave frontline workerswho are working hard on a daily basis to save lives. The League recognises their heroic efforts, working long hours to save lives in ourhospitals, clinics and other health facilities. The League wishes to convey heartfelt condolences to the families of the peoplewho have lost their lives to Covid19. This will be observed at all Nedbank Cup, GladAfrica Championship and Absa Premiership fixtures this weekend and in the coming week. -PSL Media